out.s2: When BTC'ers use Twetch to talk about Bitcoin Core, we have something of no value here üòÖ.

Today‚Äôs society normalizes weakness. No wonder why we see it everywhere.

We need strength not weakness. Intelligence not humility. Will not laziness. Courage not comfort. Geniuses not the masses.

Exalt the strong. Condemn the weak.

Ignore the noise, some talk and others take action. Criticism from those solely banking on the work of others means nothing. Their hatred lies in the fact that there‚Äôs nothing they can do to protect themselves but verbally attack their opposition.

Google Cloud Run is not ready for primetime. 
Rebuilt the K8S cluster as stock. Deployment is up; sidecar injected cleanly into pod; DB connects; ingress works. 
Ready for the weekend build.

"Ray Kurzweil predicted that by the end of 2029 the world would possibly have one #AI that matches human intelligence. What we show in this paper endorses this prediction & suggests the possibility this could happen much earlier." https://sym.re/EXjvpbW
If you want to predict Bitcoin's price, think about future production and future future-orientedness.
I‚Äôve become a Friday night drunk Twetcher üê∏ To be honest I‚Äôve had a busy week so need to catch up. üçª
Metahandle is evolving fast. Soon we will launch tag handles, value handles, exclusive handles and account handles.

Later that day, I'll try something new. Please tell me in this twetch if you like how I do it.
Hint, read my last twetches to find out what I will do.

If you don't know about metahandle.net, read this introduction
https://www.yours.org/content/introducing-metahandles--making-onchain-content-accessible-186e25f76449

Bitcoin's price goes up when either 
* people expect more future production or 
* people become more future-oriented (meaning that future production that they already expected becomes more important to them).

Dreaming is free. I dream of having 10 bsv. Can you help me ??
$ EDREAMS
Do any of you hold any BTC at all? If not when was the last time you did?

Non-mining listener ‚Äònodes‚Äô are either:

i. Service providers; or
ii. Redundant.
The value of bitcoin is future production. The price of bitcoin is expected future production.

Critics are just word terrorists.

They try to knock down with words what they couldn‚Äôt build in a lifetime.

Alright, now that we have a bigger audience here on Twetch hit me with your favorite joke. Mine:

A guy walked into a bar...

And it hurt.

It took 10 years for some of the brightest and most curious people in the world to figure out what bitcoin actually is. 

Can‚Äôt wait to see what the next 10 years holds.
